######################
# üêö SHELL SCRIPTING
######################

# Arithmetic evaluation
(( expression ))         # e.g., (( a + b ))
$(( expression ))        # e.g., echo $((a + b))

# Command substitution
$(command)               # Preferred: echo "Today is $(date)"
`command`                # Legacy: echo "Today is `date`"

# Conditional checks
[ condition ]            # Single brackets (older style)
[[ condition ]]          # Advanced test, supports pattern matching
(( condition ))          # For numeric conditions (e.g., ((a > b)))

# Examples:
if [ "$a" -gt 5 ]; then echo "OK"; fi
if [[ "$name" == K* ]]; then echo "Starts with K"; fi
if (( a % 2 == 0 )); then echo "Even"; fi

# String manipulation
str="DevOpsWorld"
echo ${str#Dev}      # OpsWorld (remove shortest match from front)
echo ${str##Dev}     # OpsWorld (same here)
echo ${str%World}    # DevOps (remove shortest match from end)
echo ${str%%World}   # DevOps (same here)

# Arithmetic via 'bc'
echo "3 * 5" | bc     # Output: 15

###############################
# üåê OSI Model (7 Layers)
###############################
1. Physical      ‚Äì Wires, signals
2. Data Link     ‚Äì MAC address, Switch
3. Network       ‚Äì IP address, Router
4. Transport     ‚Äì TCP/UDP, Ports
5. Session       ‚Äì Sessions, APIs
6. Presentation  ‚Äì Data format (encryption, compression)
7. Application   ‚Äì Apps, HTTP, DNS, FTP

üéµ Mnemonic: **Please Do Not Touch Steve‚Äôs Pet Alligator**

###############################
# üåê TCP/IP Model (4 Layers)
###############################
1. Network Access ‚Äì Ethernet, MAC
2. Internet       ‚Äì IP, ICMP
3. Transport      ‚Äì TCP, UDP
4. Application    ‚Äì HTTP, DNS, SSH

üçî Mnemonic: **Nice Indian Tasty Appetizers**

###############################
# üì° Common Internet Protocols
###############################

| Protocol | Layer       | Purpose                           | Port |
|----------|-------------|------------------------------------|------|
| IP       | Internet     | Routing & addressing               | ‚Äî    |
| ICMP     | Internet     | Ping, traceroute                   | ‚Äî    |
| TCP      | Transport    | Reliable connection                | ‚Äî    |
| UDP      | Transport    | Fast, connectionless               | ‚Äî    |
| HTTP     | Application  | Web (insecure)                     | 80   |
| HTTPS    | Application  | Secure web                         | 443  |
| FTP      | Application  | File transfer                      | 21   |
| SFTP     | Application  | Secure FTP over SSH                | 22   |
| SSH      | Application  | Secure shell (remote login)        | 22   |
| DNS      | Application  | Domain name to IP                  | 53   |
| DHCP     | Application  | IP allocation                      | 67/68|
| SMTP     | Application  | Sending email                      | 25   |
| IMAP     | Application  | Reading email                      | 143  |
| POP3     | Application  | Downloading email                  | 110  |
| NTP      | Application  | Time sync                          | 123  |
| Telnet   | Application  | Legacy terminal (insecure)         | 23   |

‚úÖ DevOps Focus:
- SSH, HTTP/HTTPS, DNS, ICMP, TCP/UDP, SFTP

üìå Mnemonic: **Some Dogs Can Hide All Food Diligently**

